-- Compass Said to Hire Banks for Bond Investor Meetings
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-01-17T13:59:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/compass-said-to-hire-banks-for-bond-investor-meetings.html
Compass Group Plc (CPG)  plans to meet
European bond investors starting on Jan. 20, according to two
people with knowledge of the arrangements.  Bank of America Corp., Barclays Capital, BNP Paribas SA,
Citigroup Inc. and  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  are organizing the
presentations and Compass may sell bonds after the meetings, the
people said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  